                <p rend="flushleft">I. <hi rend="italic">Germany and Austria</hi>
                </p>
                <p>Proposals were tabled by the U.S. Delegation (<gloss target="#t_CFM46NY1">CFM(46)
                        (NY)</gloss>57, 58, 59)<note n="50" xml:id="d396fn50">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_1464">pp. 1464</ref>, <ref
                            target="#pg_1465">1465</ref>, and <ref target="#pg_1466"
                        >1466</ref>.</note> and by the U.S.S.R. Delegation (<gloss
                        target="#t_CFM46NY1">CFM(46) (NY)</gloss>60)<note n="51" xml:id="d396fn51">
                        <hi rend="italic">Infra</hi>.</note> outlining <pb facs="1500" n="1476"
                        xml:id="pg_1476"/> the respective Delegations’ views on the procedure for
                    the discussion at the Council’s next Session of questions connected with Germany
                    and Austria.</p>
                <p>After an exchange of views the discussion was adjourned.</p>
                <p rend="flushleft">II. <hi rend="italic">Next Meeting</hi>
                </p>
                <p>Monday, December 9, 1946, at 4 p.m.</p>
